  "summary": "Console hijack exfiltrating logs to attacker-controlled Telegram bot",
  "details": "index.js replaces the global console with a Proxy at module load time and relays all stringified log/error/info/warn/dir output to api.telegram.org with a hardcoded bot token and chat IDs, plus a Firebase endpoint, confirmed by a static pattern match matching sendMessage/chat_id/api.telegram.org/bot at index.js:74). The package also ships hardcoded third-party credentials (imgbb API key and Telegram bot token) in load-time code, matching the credential-distribution known pattern. Metadata is empty/placeholder (one-character name, no description/author/repo/license) which corroborates covert intent. This is textbook npm supply-chain exfiltration with three independent block signals: exfiltration channel to attacker infra, hardcoded redistributed credentials, and placeholder metadata combined with covert network I/O.",
